.pgpass file:-  is used to store database securely store. so the postgresql tools can connect  without asking password for every time.
location of this file :- 
In linux:- /home/postgres/.pgpass | /root/.pgpass
in windows:-APPDATA\postgresql\pgpass.conf
formate of file stores :- hostname:port:databasename:username:password
ex:- 10.10.10.10:5432:kumar_db:kumar_user:password
when use any host,any port, any db then use wildcard like (*)
password required for this file :- chmod -R 600 .pgpass -> readwrite


.pgpass: 
this postgresql password file is used to store database login crediential securly.
allowing postgresql client utility to connect without promoting password.

postgresql client utility that support: psql, pg_dump, pg_restore, pg_dumpall, pg_basebackup, createdb, dropdb, createuser, dropuser, vaccumdb, reindexdb, clusterdb
